		<div id="siteNotice"><script type='text/javascript'>if (wgNotice != '') document.writeln(wgNotice);</script></div>		<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading">Central Authentication Service</h1>
		<div id="bodyContent">
			<h3 id="siteSub">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</h3>
			<div id="contentSub"></div>
									<div id="jump-to-nav">Jump to: <a href="#column-one">navigation</a>, <a href="#searchInput">search</a></div>			<!-- start content -->
			<p>The <b>Central Authentication Service</b> (CAS) is a <a href="/wiki/Single_sign-on" title="Single sign-on">single sign-on</a> protocol for the <a href="/wiki/Web" title="Web">web</a>. Its purpose is to permit a user to access multiple applications while providing their credentials (such as userid and password) only once. It also allows web applications to authenticate users without gaining access to a user's security credentials, such as a password. The name <i>CAS</i> also refers to a software package that implements this protocol.</p>
